# Files excluded from the EAS Build upload archive. EAS will reinstall
# dependencies and rebuild all native artifacts on its build servers, so the
# upload only needs source + config + the prebuilt `android/` project (minus
# its build outputs).
#
# Syntax mirrors .gitignore. EAS falls back to .gitignore when this file is
# absent, but our .gitignore omits `android/` (we commit the prebuild folder
# so Gradle uses our edits), which means the giant Gradle build outputs would
# otherwise ride along on every upload.

# --- Dependencies (reinstalled by EAS) ----------------------------------
node_modules/

# --- Android Gradle / native build outputs ------------------------------
android/build/
android/app/build/
android/.gradle/
android/.cxx/
android/app/.cxx/
android/captures/
android/local.properties

# --- iOS build outputs (not building iOS, but cheap insurance) ----------
ios/build/
ios/Pods/
ios/DerivedData/

# --- Expo / Metro caches ------------------------------------------------
.expo/
.expo-shared/
dist/
web-build/
.metro-health-check*

# --- Test / coverage output --------------------------------------------
coverage/

# --- Local logs and OS junk --------------------------------------------
*.log
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*
.DS_Store

# --- Local build artifacts ---------------------------------------------
*.apk
*.aab
*.tsbuildinfo

# --- VCS internals (EAS doesn't need history) --------------------------
.git/
